# ---------- Helpers: synthetic dataset generators ----------

make_blobs <- function(n_samples=1000, n_features=2, centers=4, cluster_std=1, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  if (length(centers)==1) {
    C <- matrix(runif(centers * n_features, -10, 10), nrow=centers)
  } else {
    C <- as.matrix(centers)
  }
  k <- nrow(C)
  labels <- sample.int(k, n_samples, replace=TRUE)
  X <- matrix(NA_real_, n_samples, n_features)
  for (i in seq_len(k)) {
    idx <- which(labels == i)
    if (length(idx)) {
      X[idx, ] <- sweep(matrix(rnorm(length(idx)*n_features, sd=cluster_std),
                               ncol=n_features), 2, C[i,], "+")
    }
  }
  list(X=X, y=labels)
}

# --- make_moons ---
make_moons <- function(n_samples = 500, noise = 0.07, seed = 42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  n  <- n_samples %/% 2
  t1 <- runif(n, 0, pi)
  x1 <- cbind(cos(t1), sin(t1))
  t2 <- runif(n, 0, pi)
  x2 <- cbind(1 - cos(t2), -sin(t2) + 0.5)

  X <- rbind(x1, x2)  # (2n x 2)
  if (noise > 0) {
    X <- X + matrix(rnorm(nrow(X) * ncol(X), sd = noise), ncol = ncol(X))
  }
  y <- c(rep(1, n), rep(2, n))
  list(X = X, y = y)
}

# --- make_circles ---
make_circles <- function(n_samples = 500, factor = 0.5, noise = 0.05, seed = 42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  n  <- n_samples %/% 2
  t1 <- runif(n, 0, 2*pi)
  t2 <- runif(n, 0, 2*pi)
  X1 <- cbind(cos(t1), sin(t1))
  X2 <- factor * cbind(cos(t2), sin(t2))

  X <- rbind(X1, X2)  # (2n x 2)
  if (noise > 0) {
    X <- X + matrix(rnorm(nrow(X) * ncol(X), sd = noise), ncol = ncol(X))
  }
  y <- c(rep(1, n), rep(2, n))
  list(X = X, y = y)
}

# ---------- 1) Measure K-means vs DBSCAN time & memory ----------

measure_clustering <- function(fit_fun, X) {
  gc()
  t <- system.time({
    labels <- fit_fun(X)
  })[["elapsed"]]
  mem_mb <- as.numeric(object.size(labels) + object.size(X)) / (1024^2) # approx
  c(time_sec=t, peak_mem_mb=mem_mb)
}

# 5000 x 10 blobs
blobs_5k <- make_blobs(n_samples=5000, n_features=10, centers=5, cluster_std=1, seed=42)
X_5k <- blobs_5k$X

kmeans_fit_fun <- function(X) {
  kmeans(X, centers=5, nstart=10)$cluster
}
dbscan_fit_fun <- function(X) {
  dbscan::dbscan(scale(X), eps=0.5, minPts=5)$cluster
}

m_kmeans <- measure_clustering(kmeans_fit_fun, X_5k)
m_dbscan <- measure_clustering(dbscan_fit_fun, X_5k)

cat(sprintf("K-means: Time = %.4f sec, Approx Peak Memory = %.4f MB\n", m_kmeans[1], m_kmeans[2]))
cat(sprintf("DBSCAN:  Time = %.4f sec, Approx Peak Memory = %.4f MB\n", m_dbscan[1], m_dbscan[2]))

# ---- helper: map labels -> colours (0/NA -> grey) ----
.col_from_labels <- function(lab, n) {
  if (is.null(lab) || length(lab) == 0L) lab <- rep(NA_integer_, n)
  lab2 <- lab
  lab2[lab2 == 0] <- NA_integer_
  cols <- rep("grey80", length(lab2))
  idx  <- !is.na(lab2)
  if (any(idx)) {
    u   <- sort(unique(lab2[idx]))
    pal <- grDevices::hcl.colors(length(u), "Dark 3", rev = TRUE)
    map <- setNames(pal, u)
    cols[idx] <- map[as.character(lab2[idx])]
  }
  cols
}

algorithms <- list(
  "K-means"                  = function(X) kmeans(X, centers=4, nstart=10)$cluster,
  "Agglomerative - Single"   = function(X) cutree(hclust(dist(X), method="single"),   k=4),
  "Agglomerative - Complete" = function(X) cutree(hclust(dist(X), method="complete"), k=4),
  "Agglomerative - Average"  = function(X) cutree(hclust(dist(X), method="average"),  k=4),

  # ---- BIRCH via stream (returns labels; silent skip if pkg missing) ----
  "BIRCH" = function(X) {
    if (!requireNamespace("stream", quietly = TRUE))
      return(rep(NA_integer_, nrow(X)))

    Xs <- scale(X)
    micro <- stream::DSC_BIRCH(threshold = 0.15, branching = 50, maxLeaf = 50)
    macro <- stream::DSC_Kmeans(k = 4)
    dsc   <- stream::DSC_TwoStage(micro = micro, macro = macro)

    dsd <- stream::DSD_Memory(as.data.frame(Xs))
    stream::update(dsc, dsd, n = nrow(Xs))
    stream::recluster(dsc)  # <-- macro clusters

    lab <- stream::predict(dsc, as.data.frame(Xs), type = "macro")
    if (length(lab) == 0L || all(is.na(lab))) {
      lab <- stream::predict(dsc, as.data.frame(Xs), type = "micro")
    }
    as.integer(lab)
  },

  # ---- DBSCAN (silent skip if pkg missing) ----
  "DBSCAN" = function(X) {
    if (!requireNamespace("dbscan", quietly = TRUE))
      return(rep(NA_integer_, nrow(X)))
    dbscan::dbscan(scale(X), eps = 0.2, minPts = 5)$cluster
  }
)

nrow_plot <- length(datasets)
ncol_plot <- length(algorithms) + 1

op <- par(mfrow=c(nrow_plot, ncol_plot), mar=c(2.5,2.5,2.2,0.5))

}

# ---------- 5) DBSCAN from scratch (pure R) ----------

euclidean_distance <- function(p1, p2) sqrt(sum((p1 - p2)^2))

region_query <- function(D, i, eps) {
  d2 <- rowSums((t(t(D) - D[i, ]))^2)
  which(sqrt(d2) <= eps)
}

expand_cluster <- function(D, labels, i, cluster_id, eps, min_pts) {
  neighbors <- region_query(D, i, eps)
  if (length(neighbors) < min_pts) {
    labels[i] <- -1L
    return(list(labels=labels, expanded=FALSE))
  } else {
    labels[i] <- cluster_id
    queue <- neighbors
    head <- 1L
    while (head <= length(queue)) {
      p <- queue[head]; head <- head + 1L
      if (labels[p] == -1L) labels[p] <- cluster_id
      if (labels[p] == 0L) {
        labels[p] <- cluster_id
        nbor <- region_query(D, p, eps)
        if (length(nbor) >= min_pts) {
          queue <- c(queue, nbor)
        }
      }
    }
    return(list(labels=labels, expanded=TRUE))
  }
}

dbscan_from_scratch <- function(D, eps, min_pts) {
  n <- nrow(D)
  labels <- integer(n)  # 0 = unvisited; -1 = noise; >0 = cluster id
  cluster_id <- 0L
  for (i in seq_len(n)) {
    if (labels[i] != 0L) next
    res <- expand_cluster(D, labels, i, cluster_id + 1L, eps, min_pts)
    labels <- res$labels
    if (isTRUE(res$expanded)) cluster_id <- cluster_id + 1L
  }
  labels
}

mm <- make_moons(n_samples=300, noise=0.05, seed=42)
labels_scratch <- dbscan_from_scratch(mm$X, eps=0.2, min_pts=5)
plot(mm$X, col=labels_scratch + 1L, pch=19, cex=.9, main="DBSCAN from Scratch")

# ---------- 7) Custom 'Database 1/2/3' (version A) ----------

make_database1_A <- function(n_cluster=200, n_noise=100, radius=0.3, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  theta <- runif(n_cluster, 0, 2*pi)
  r <- radius * sqrt(runif(n_cluster))
  cluster <- cbind(r*cos(theta), r*sin(theta))
  noise <- matrix(runif(n_noise*2, -1, 1), ncol=2)
  rbind(cluster, noise)
}

make_database2_A <- function(n_points=200, noise=0.02, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  t <- seq(0, 4*pi, length.out=n_points)
  x1 <- cbind(sin(t), cos(t)) + matrix(rnorm(2*n_points, sd=noise), ncol=2)
  x2 <- cbind(sin(t+pi), cos(t+pi)) + matrix(rnorm(2*n_points, sd=noise), ncol=2)
  rbind(x1, x2)
}

make_database3_A <- function(n_blobs=4, n_points=50, n_noise=100, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  centers <- rbind(c(-0.8, 0.8), c(0.8, 0.8), c(0, -0.5), c(0.5,-0.2))
  clusters <- do.call(rbind, lapply(seq_len(nrow(centers)), function(i) {
    matrix(rnorm(n_points*2, sd=0.05), ncol=2) + matrix(centers[i,], ncol=2, nrow=n_points, byrow=TRUE)
  }))
  noise <- matrix(runif(n_noise*2, -1, 1), ncol=2)
  rbind(clusters, noise)
}

db1 <- make_database1_A()
db2 <- make_database2_A()
db3 <- make_database3_A()

op <- par(mfrow=c(1,3), mar=c(2,2,2,1))
plot(db1, pch=19, cex=.5, main="Database 1")
plot(db2, pch=19, cex=.5, main="Database 2")
plot(db3, pch=19, cex=.5, main="Database 3")
par(op)

# ---------- 8) Custom 'Database 1/2/3' (version B, incl. spirals) ----------

make_database1_B <- function(n_cluster=200, n_noise=200, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  cluster <- matrix(rnorm(n_cluster*2, sd=0.1), ncol=2)
  noise <- matrix(runif(n_noise*2, -1, 1), ncol=2)
  rbind(cluster, noise)
}

make_database2_B <- function(n_points=500, noise=0.02, seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  n <- n_points %/% 2
  theta <- seq(0, 3*pi, length.out=n)
  r <- seq(0.1, 1, length.out=n)
  x1 <- cbind(r*cos(theta), r*sin(theta)) + matrix(rnorm(2*n, sd=noise), ncol=2)
  x2 <- cbind(r*cos(theta+pi), r*sin(theta+pi)) + matrix(rnorm(2*n, sd=noise), ncol=2)
  rbind(x1, x2)
}

make_database3_B <- function(seed=42) {
  set.seed(seed)
  centers <- rbind(c(0,0), c(1,1), c(-1,1), c(0.5,-1))
  clusters <- do.call(rbind, lapply(seq_len(nrow(centers)), function(i) {
    matrix(rnorm(40*2, sd=0.1), ncol=2) + matrix(centers[i,], ncol=2, nrow=40, byrow=TRUE)
  }))
  noise <- matrix(runif(150*2, -1, 1), ncol=2)
  rbind(clusters, noise)
}

db1B <- make_database1_B()
db2B <- make_database2_B()
db3B <- make_database3_B()

# ---------- 11) Runtime growth O(n) vs O(n^2) ----------

simulate_on <- function(n) {
  t <- system.time({
    s <- 0L
    for (i in seq_len(n)) s <- s + i
  })["elapsed"]
  as.numeric(t)
}
simulate_on2 <- function(n) {
  t <- system.time({
    s <- 0L
    for (i in seq_len(n)) for (j in seq_len(n)) s <- s + i + j
  })["elapsed"]
  as.numeric(t)
}

for (n in c(500, 1000, 2000)) {
  t1 <- simulate_on(n)
  t2 <- simulate_on2(n)
  cat(sprintf("n=%4d | O(n): %.5fs | O(n^2): %.5fs\n", n, t1, t2))
}

n=1000 | O(n): 0.00000s | O(n^2): 0.11500s

# ---------- 12) Plot growth curves for Big-O ----------

n <- seq(10, 2000, length.out=200)
on      <- n
onlogn  <- n * (log(n, base=2))
on2     <- n^2

on      <- on      / max(on)
onlogn  <- onlogn  / max(onlogn)
on2     <- on2     / max(on2)

plot(n, on, type="l", lwd=2, xlab="n (data size)", ylab="Relative growth",
     main="Growth of Big-O Complexities")
lines(n, onlogn, lwd=2)
lines(n, on2, lwd=2)
legend("topleft", legend=c("O(n)", "O(n log n)", "O(n^2)"), lwd=2, bty="n")
grid()
